libuvc
------------------------------------------
libuvc is a cross-platform library for USB video devices, built atop libusb.
It enables fine-grained control over USB video devices exporting the standard
USB Video Class (UVC) interface, enabling developers to write drivers for
previously unsupported devices, or just access UVC devices in a generic
fashion.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.9.0-3
  libusb1.0-1.0.21-1
  libusb1.0-devel-1.0.21-1
  libuvc-devel-0.0.6-1bl1
  libuvc0-0.0.6-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.24.1-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2
  python-2.7.13-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/ktossell/libuvc

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/ktossell/libuvc/archive/v0.0.6.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libuvc-0.0.6-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libuvc-0.0.6-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libuvc-0.0.6-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libuvc-0.0.6-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libuvc0-0.0.6-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libuvc-devel-0.0.6-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

